frameDefinitions: There is a gradable amount of light in a particular Location.
This frame contains words for individuals, i.e. humans, with respect to their Religion.
In this frame, an Agent or Cause changes the duration of an Event.
This frame describes food and meal preparation.
A Color serves as a landmark in color-space, either a point-like landmark (e.g. burnt sienna) or a broader region (e.g. blue).
This frame covers LUs that describe the race of a Person.
frameExamples: The small print was bearly readable by the light of the very <t>dim</t> torch.
The bells call the <t><fex name='Person'>faithful</fex></t> to evensong DNI
Don't let him <t>prolong</t> the discussion to an absurd length.
Caitlin <t>baked</t> some cookies from the pre-packaged dough.
I really like that shade of <t>blue</t>.
Carlos is <t>hispanic</t>, or so he says.
listRoleDefinitions: The place whose amout of light is being described.  The <fen>Location</fen> can also be a location in time, as seen in the second example below:
The entity from which the light eminates.
The religious belief system that the <fen>Person</fen> follows.
The sentient entity that changes the duration of the <fen>Event</fen>.
An event that causes the change in Event duration.
The time at which the change in duration of the Event is caused.
The <fen>Produced_food</fen> is the result of a <fen>Cook</fen>'s efforts.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the cooking creation occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the cooking creation occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Entity</fen> described by the <fen>Color</fen>.
A position in color-space, generally used to describe the quality of some <fen>Entity</fen>.
The Person whose race is being described.
listRoleExamples: She hid from the man in a dark <fex>corner</fex>.
A dim <fex>lamp</fex> swung over the entrance to the castle.
Don't let <fex>him</fex> prolong the discussion to an absurd length.
Don't let him prolong <fex>the discussion</fex> to an absurd length.
<fex>Rain</fex> so cruelly cut short the game against Bangladesh.
<fex>Last week</fex>, he unnecessarily prolonged the agony, thinking that he could tough it out.
Drew baked an apple pie <fex>at six int he morning</fex>.
Drew prepared the soup <fex> in the kitchen</fex>.
